data.description: Welcome to this affordable, cozy and newly renovated 1922 bungalow. You'll feel right at home when you walk in on the wood-like luxury vinyl plank flooring accentuated with new interior paint and new trim throughout. There's plenty of curb appeal with the craftsman front door, and new siding on the front of the house. The kitchen has been updated with new cabinets and is accented with a subway tile backsplash, faux-marble tops & new sink with garbage disposal. You will also find a new dishwasher, refrigerator, microwave, and electric range. Likewise, the bathroom has been updated including a new bathtub, vanity, sink and new plumbing connections under the house. Relax in the Florida outdoors on the large deck in the privacy of the fenced backyard. This home also features updated electrical wiring  with a new service panel, newer A/C unit (2021) and a solid foundation, supported by steel beams. Plus, there's a transferable termite bond. This one is worth a look!
